It is a crisp story, being let to be real and believable. There are a lot of twists and turns. Some people like Jame Gordon who believe on doing everything right have to bent for good. 

It is a realistic story in a mythical city of Gotham. Lovely to watch and know the background of much celebrated super heroes. 

This serial is slick and smartly tailored for the audience. Till fourth episode it has not lost an inch and is gaining ground (audience).

Robin Lord Taylor (Penguin) is just admirable and he is giving performance of his lifetime.

Gotham depicts the life in a damned city which is in a chaos and nothing is controllable.

Wayne enterprise is not yet fully explored, as Master Bruce Wayne.